dataIdInfo.idAbs: The Ghana hydrology_line layer is a linear feature representing all major rivers, minor rivers, streams, channels, drains, creeks etc in Ghana. Also indicated are annual and perennial water channels in Ghana.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: The data reported in this table was developed by the Ghana hydrological Services and Water Resource Commission and Centre for Remote Sensing and Geographic Information Services (CERSGIS). The purpose of this data is to create a digital layers of linear hydrological features (Rivers/Streams) in Ghana to enable monitoring and analysis of these features. This will help in flood risk modelling, water security etc.
